p.Config[\"max_attempts\"]` in the `Execute()` method\n  - Converts to integer with `strconv.Atoi()`\n  - Compares against `readAttemptCount()` to enforce retry limit\n  - Returns \"give-up\" result when max attempts reached (line 76)\n  - Attempt counter management at lines 452-484 (read/increment/reset functions)\n\n**Prompt Test:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go` (lines 125-138)\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_MaxAttemptsReached`: Tests retry limiting behavior\n  - Confirms \"give-up\" result when `max_attempts = 2` limit is exceeded\n\n### 5. **Actual Workflow Files Using max_attempts**\n\n**Default Template:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` (line 23)\n  - Scaffold template includes `max_attempts = 2` in the fix step\n\n**Deployed Workflows:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` (line 14): `max_attempts = 2` on fix step\n- `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche` (line 24): `max_attempts = 2` on fix step\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/develop.cloche` (line 29): `max_attempts = 4` on fix step\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/flaky.cloche`: No max_attempts (flaky test demo)\n- Multiple evolution snapshots in `/workspace/.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`: Various max_attempts values including \"2\"\n\n### Key Design Points:\n1. **String storage**: Stored as a string in Config, converted to int at runtime only\n2. **Per-step configuration**: Each step can have its own max_attempts limit\n3. **Attempt tracking**: Uses `.cloche/attempt_count/` directory to persist attempt counts between runs\n4. **Reset on success**: Attempt counter resets on successful completion so limits apply to consecutive failures only\n5. **Result fallback**: Returns \"give-up\" result to workflow when limit exceeded, allowing graceful handling"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3e33ef80a5b90e9c (use SendMessage with to: 'a3e33ef80a5b90e9c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46405\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 51753</usa